<h4 id="2021">2021</h4>
<p>Allen, R.J., L.W. Horowitz, V. Naik, N. Oshima, F.M. O'Connor, S. Turnock, S. Shim, P. Le Sager, T. van Noije, <span class="gissauthor">K. Tsigaridis</span>, <span class="gissauthor">S.E. Bauer</span>, L.T. Sentman, J.G John, C. Broderick, M. Deushi, G.A. Folberth, S. Fujimori, and W.J. Collins, 2021: <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/abs/al04700w.html">Significant climate benefits from near-term climate forcer mitigation in spite of aerosol reductions</a>. <cite>Environ. Res. Lett.</cite>, <b>16</b>, no. 3, 034010, doi:10.1088/1748-9326/abe06b.</p>
